The paper discusses the use of deep neural networks in molecular applications, which falls under the category of machine learning. The focus of the paper is on Bayesian neural networks and their ability to quantify uncertainty in molecular property prediction. This topic is closely related to several sub-categories of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computational engineering (cs.CE), computer vision (cs.CV), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). Therefore, these are the most likely sub-categories for this paper.
